you've added a new element

261
00:12:12,404 --> 00:12:13,704
to your morning routine.

262
00:12:13,772 --> 00:12:15,272
You're screaming.

263
00:12:16,908 --> 00:12:19,210
Okay, yeah.

264
00:12:19,278 --> 00:12:21,078
I scream for ten seconds,
but then--

265
00:12:21,146 --> 00:12:25,817
then I go
and have my breakfast.

266
00:12:25,884 --> 00:12:28,886
Or are you angry
about something?

267
00:12:28,954 --> 00:12:30,088
It might help
if you discuss it.

268
00:12:30,155 --> 00:12:32,290
I...no.
I don't want to discuss it.

269
00:12:32,357 --> 00:12:34,959
I scream, so we don't have
to discuss it.

270
00:12:35,027 --> 00:12:36,227
Right, I see.

271
00:12:36,295 --> 00:12:38,963
You know, you have every reason
to be angry.

272
00:12:39,031 --> 00:12:41,665
The government
took you away from your home,

273
00:12:41,733 --> 00:12:47,738
put a chip in your neck--
they killed her.

274
00:12:47,805 --> 00:12:50,040
They killed her--
Anna.

275
00:12:50,107 --> 00:12:52,709
They shot her in the head.
She was my friend.

276
00:13:02,953 --> 00:13:04,453
Gary, it's a--
it's a healthy thing

277
00:13:04,521 --> 00:13:06,255
to express yourself.

278
00:13:06,323 --> 00:13:07,957
I'm glad that you are.

279
00:13:08,025 --> 00:13:11,361
Um, maybe you can find
a way to do it

280
00:13:11,429 --> 00:13:15,733
without terrifying
your mother.

281
00:13:17,869 --> 00:13:20,270
[Wincing]

282
00:13:20,338 --> 00:13:23,040
Bill!
Are you okay?

283
00:13:23,108 --> 00:13:24,508
No, I'm not.
Don't worry about it.

284
00:13:24,576 --> 00:13:26,577
What you got for me?

285
00:13:26,645 --> 00:13:27,912
Rachel got the name
of our acid spitter--

286
00:13:27,980 --> 00:13:29,681
Ivan Bazevich...

287
00:13:29,748 --> 00:13:31,549
did a stretch upstate,
no known address.

288
00:13:31,617 --> 00:13:32,517
So how do we find him?

289
00:13:32,584 --> 00:13:35,221
Well, we know he's a fighter.

290
00:13:35,288 --> 00:13:37,123
Hey.

291
00:13:37,191 --> 00:13:40,059
I heard things
got pretty rough last night.

292
00:13:40,127 --> 00:13:42,662
Things get rough every night.
You take your chances.

293
00:13:42,730 --> 00:13:43,796
So when's the next fight?

294
00:13:43,864 --> 00:13:45,565
For you?
[Laughs] Never.

295
00:13:45,632 --> 00:13:47,500
You ain't cut out for this.

296
00:13:47,568 --> 00:13:51,170
Hey, wait.
I-I'll work with him.

297
00:13:51,238 --> 00:13:53,839
- This guy, Kat?
- Guy's got moves.

298
00:13:53,907 --> 00:13:55,708
He just doesn't know
how to use 'em.

299
00:13:55,776 --> 00:13:56,909
Give him another shot.

300
00:13:56,977 --> 00:13:58,210
For you, fine.

301
00:13:58,278 --> 00:14:01,848
But I don't see it.

302
00:14:01,915 --> 00:14:03,550
So I know all their tricks,

303
00:14:03,618 --> 00:14:06,920
so if you want to win
next time,

304
00:14:06,988 --> 00:14:08,889
give me a call.

305
00:14:08,956 --> 00:14:10,190
I'm Kat.

306
00:14:10,258 --> 00:14:11,859
So why do you
want to help me out?

307
00:14:11,927 --> 00:14:14,095
So I can bet on you,
cash in.

308
00:14:17,799 --> 00:14:20,501
[Laughing]
Okay, later.

309
00:14:24,586 --> 00:14:26,420
[cereal pouring]

310
00:14:34,628 --> 00:14:36,028
What's all this?

311
00:14:36,096 --> 00:14:38,664
Dr. Rosen said that
I should find a way to scream

312
00:14:38,732 --> 00:14:41,199
without terrifying you,
so I did--I'm moving out.

313
00:14:41,267 --> 00:14:42,534
What?

314
00:14:42,601 --> 00:14:44,302
Yeah, I'm gonna go live
at my office.

315
00:14:44,370 --> 00:14:46,705
What are you talking about?

316
00:14:46,772 --> 00:14:48,006
Sandra,
I know you're upset,

317
00:14:48,074 --> 00:14:51,042
but I did not recommend
that Gary leave home.

318
00:14:51,110 --> 00:14:53,011
No, but that was your solution
for Rachel.

319
00:14:53,079 --> 00:14:55,146
Why's it different for me?
W-why's that not my solution?

320
00:14:55,214 --> 00:14:56,715
Gary, you are not
going anywhere.

321
00:14:56,783 --> 00:14:58,583
I want to do
what I want to do.

322
00:14:58,651 --> 00:15:00,252
You know what? You're not
going to work today either.

323
00:15:00,320 --> 00:15:02,220
Yeah, Mom, come on,
of course I'm going to work.

324
00:15:02,288 --> 00:15:03,455
I go into work every day.

325
00:15:03,523 --> 00:15:04,723
They need me there.
I need you here.

326
00:15:04,791 --> 00:15:06,725
No! You don't need me.
Go in the house.

327
00:15:06,793 --> 00:15:08,127
I'm going to work.

328
00:15:08,194 --> 00:15:10,562
Gary!
Gary, it's, uh--

329
00:15:10,630 --> 00:15:13,065
it's quite all right if you
don't come to work today.

330
00:15:13,132 --> 00:15:14,700
There's nothing urgent,

331
00:15:14,768 --> 00:15:17,803
and if we need you,
w-we'll call.

332
00:15:17,871 --> 00:15:19,772
And I think it would be
a good idea

333
00:15:19,839 --> 00:15:23,609
if we all sat down very soon
and discussed your future.

334
00:15:23,677 --> 00:15:26,145
My future?

335
00:15:26,213 --> 00:15:28,047
Yeah, <i>my</i> future.
Yeah.

336
00:15:28,115 --> 00:15:30,282
Yeah.

337
00:15:30,350 --> 00:15:31,183
[Sighs]

338
00:15:35,722 --> 00:15:37,156
[Door closes]

339
00:15:37,224 --> 00:15:39,191
We're still focused on
Bazevich as our killer.

340
00:15:39,259 --> 00:15:40,893
We finally got his records
from D.O.D.

341
00:15:40,960 --> 00:15:42,995
Well, are we any closer
to finding this guy?

342
00:15:43,062 --> 00:15:45,430
Cops have been by all his
usual hangouts--no sign of him.

343
00:15:45,498 --> 00:15:46,731
Harken's checking a lead,

344
00:15:46,799 --> 00:15:48,600
but look, if you ask me,
these Alpha fights

345
00:15:48,668 --> 00:15:49,768
are still our best bet.

346
00:15:49,835 --> 00:15:51,436
Just as long
as it's a stakeout

347
00:15:51,503 --> 00:15:53,404
and no more fighting.

348
00:15:53,472 --> 00:15:55,840
I wasn't the one fighting.

349
00:15:55,907 --> 00:15:57,674
[Chuckles]
To be honest with you,

350
00:15:57,742 --> 00:15:59,176
I don't know
if we can keep him away.

351
00:15:59,244 --> 00:16:00,711
I mean, the guy's
in training right now

352
00:16:00,778 --> 00:16:03,713
for his next fight.

