00:24:36,569 --> 00:24:37,969
What are you--oh!
[Giggles]

519
00:24:40,006 --> 00:24:42,241
Gary, you can't live
in your office.

520
00:24:42,308 --> 00:24:44,042
You've gotta be practical.

521
00:24:44,110 --> 00:24:45,444
I am being practical.

522
00:24:45,511 --> 00:24:47,245
You won't have to hear me
scream every day.

523
00:24:47,313 --> 00:24:48,580
But you need to be safe.

524
00:24:48,648 --> 00:24:50,482
Yeah, it is safe.
It's safer.

525
00:24:50,550 --> 00:24:52,884
I won't have to drive
to work anymore,

526
00:24:52,952 --> 00:24:55,254
'cause people die
in car crashes all the time.

527
00:24:55,321 --> 00:24:59,257
And Dr. Rosen--
he forgets to signal a lot.

528
00:24:59,325 --> 00:25:01,459
And anyway, the building
has security, so there--

529
00:25:01,527 --> 00:25:04,829
it's more secure
than this place.

530
00:25:04,897 --> 00:25:08,299
Don't you tell me
you support him in this.

531
00:25:08,366 --> 00:25:10,334
I think we both
need to support Gary

532
00:25:10,402 --> 00:25:12,669
in whatever steps
he needs to take

533
00:25:12,737 --> 00:25:16,406
towards his independence.

534
00:25:16,474 --> 00:25:18,208
But this is too big a step.

535
00:25:23,815 --> 00:25:26,283
For him or for you?

536
00:25:35,626 --> 00:25:38,862
Yeah, let me get a turkey dog
with everything.

537
00:25:38,929 --> 00:25:39,996
Coming up.
And for you?

538
00:25:40,064 --> 00:25:41,431
What do you want?

539
00:25:41,499 --> 00:25:43,599
Uh, what do
they taste like?

540
00:25:43,667 --> 00:25:45,602
They taste like hot dogs.

541
00:25:45,669 --> 00:25:47,571
What, you've never had
a hot dog before?

542
00:25:47,638 --> 00:25:49,406
Must have, right?

543
00:25:49,473 --> 00:25:51,341
Um, yeah, I'll just have
the same thing.

544
00:25:51,409 --> 00:25:52,576
All right,
give me two, please.

545
00:25:52,644 --> 00:25:55,012
Thanks.
Thanks.

546
00:25:55,079 --> 00:25:57,181
- So you coming tonight?
- Hell, yeah.

547
00:25:57,248 --> 00:25:59,450
There's gonna be
a boatload of people there

548
00:25:59,518 --> 00:26:00,885
with deep pockets,

549
00:26:00,953 --> 00:26:03,421
so you got to crush everyone
so we can rake it.

550
00:26:03,489 --> 00:26:07,158
Yeah, you need
some of this here.

551
00:26:07,226 --> 00:26:09,027
Some peppers and...

552
00:26:09,095 --> 00:26:12,598
so what about, uh, Bazevich?
Think he'll be there?

553
00:26:12,665 --> 00:26:15,934
You have, like, a man-crush
on him or something?

554
00:26:16,002 --> 00:26:17,169
How should I know
if he's coming?

555
00:26:17,237 --> 00:26:18,604
What do you mean
how should you know?

556
00:26:18,672 --> 00:26:20,573
I thought you knew everything
about these fights.

557
00:26:20,641 --> 00:26:22,141
How did you get involved
with them anyway?

558
00:26:22,209 --> 00:26:24,577
Just kind of
found myself there.

559
00:26:24,645 --> 00:26:27,346
These are amazing.
This is good.

560
00:26:27,414 --> 00:26:28,414
- You like that?
- Yeah.

561
00:26:28,482 --> 00:26:30,182
That's good stuff.

562
00:26:30,250 --> 00:26:34,187
What do you mean
you just found yourself there?

563
00:26:34,255 --> 00:26:38,791
I. I have this thing
where I can't remember

564
00:26:38,859 --> 00:26:43,296
anything that happened, like,
more than a month ago.

565
00:26:43,364 --> 00:26:44,664
Like, a month from now,

566
00:26:44,732 --> 00:26:49,203
I won't remember this
or you or the hot dog.

567
00:26:49,271 --> 00:26:51,372
- You serious?
- Mm-hmm.

568
00:26:51,440 --> 00:26:53,975
My brain's wired to,
like, make room

569
00:26:54,043 --> 00:26:55,910
for all the new crap
I learn, you know?

570
00:26:55,978 --> 00:26:58,613
Yeah, but what about
your family, your home?

571
00:26:58,681 --> 00:27:01,216
Home's the fights for now.

572
00:27:01,284 --> 00:27:04,720
You got to be careful.
That's a rough crowd.

573
00:27:04,787 --> 00:27:07,489
Don't get all "Papa bear"
on me, okay?

574
00:27:07,557 --> 00:27:11,059
I've been taking care
of myself for...

575
00:27:11,127 --> 00:27:13,729
Well, I can't remember,
but it--it's been a long time.

576
00:27:13,796 --> 00:27:15,997
It's got to be lonely,
though.

577
00:27:21,938 --> 00:27:23,838
It's stupid, though.

578
00:27:23,906 --> 00:27:25,807
I don't know
why libraries do this.

579
00:27:25,875 --> 00:27:28,777
Dr. Rosen, it's just
a big waste of space.

580
00:27:28,845 --> 00:27:31,246
They could fit everything
in here just on one microchip.

581
00:27:31,314 --> 00:27:32,648
Inside voice, please, Gary.

582
00:27:32,715 --> 00:27:34,216
What?

583
00:27:34,284 --> 00:27:35,851
Inside voice, please.

584
00:27:35,919 --> 00:27:40,088
My inside voice
is too quiet.

585
00:27:40,156 --> 00:27:44,559
Well, split the difference,
then, huh?

586
00:27:44,627 --> 00:27:47,162
Oh, we are fortunate
this university

587
00:27:47,230 --> 00:27:50,231
preserved its newspapers.

588
00:27:50,299 --> 00:27:52,100
[Door closes]

589
00:27:56,405 --> 00:27:58,239
[Sighs]

590
00:28:02,811 --> 00:28:06,446
Jacob.
This is a surprise.

591
00:28:06,514 --> 00:28:10,583
You're making
a presentation tonight.

592
00:28:10,651 --> 00:28:13,453
Your abilities
are extraordinary.

593
00:28:15,189 --> 00:28:18,091
Cancel your presentation,
Zac.

594
00:28:18,159 --> 00:28:20,894
Promise to never speak
of what I can do.

595
00:28:20,961 --> 00:28:22,863
I can't, Jacob.

596
00:28:22,930 --> 00:28:25,632
It's too important
to keep to ourselves.

597
00:28:27,968 --> 00:28:30,570
[Gasps]

598
00:28:30,638 --> 00:28:33,640
[Gasping and choking]

599
00:28:42,651 --> 00:28:45,519
This crowd is hot tonight.

600
00:28:45,587 --> 00:28:47,354
Well, Rocky, try and remember
why we're here.

601
00:28:47,422 --> 00:28:48,689
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

602
00:28:48,757 --> 00:28:50,324
You see Kat anywhere?

603
00:28:50,392 --> 00:28:51,859
Don't worry about that kid.
She can take care of herself.

604
00:28:51,927 --> 00:28:53,227
No, look, she can't take care
of herself.

605
00:28:53,295 --> 00:28:55,229
She forgets things.
She could be lost or confused.

606
00:28:55,297 --> 00:28:57,298
I think she's gonna be okay.
Just stay focused.

607
00:28:57,366 --> 00:28:58,499
All right, all right,
all right.

608
00:28:58,567 --> 00:28:59,734
Let's go, let's go,
let's go.

609
00:28:59,801 --> 00:29:01,703
Who is gonna start the show?

610
00:29:01,770 --> 00:29:03,071
I will.

611
00:29:03,138 --> 00:29:05,573
No, no, no, no, no, man.
We need a real fighter.

612
00:29:05,641 --> 00:29:08,176
Bring it on.

613
00:29:08,244 --> 00:29:10,245
All right, all right,
we got some fresh meat.

614
00:29:10,312 --> 00:29:12,514
Now, who is gonna
be the challenger?

615
00:29:12,582 --> 00:29:14,449
Rubberman!

616
00:29:14,517 --> 00:29:17,252
[Crowd shouting]

617
00:29:17,320 --> 00:29:20,522
[Laughs]

618
00:29:20,590 --> 00:29:22,825
I'm gonna remember
to send you some flowers.

619
00:29:22,893 --> 00:29:24,994
All right, ladies and gentlemen,
you know what time it is.

620
00:29:25,062 --> 00:29:26,762
Time to place your bets!

621
00:29:35,607 --> 00:29:38,242
There's nothing to control.

622
00:29:38,309 --> 00:29:40,511
You don't have
to reach for it,

623
00:29:40,579 --> 00:29:42,914
'cause it's part of you.

624
00:29:42,981 --> 00:29:45,349
When you want it,
it'll be there.

625
00:29:45,417 --> 00:29:47,885
[Crowd shouting]

626
00:29:53,425 --> 00:29:56,226
[Cheering]

627
00:30:04,869 --> 00:30:07,637
Unit one still clear.

628
00:30:07,705 --> 00:30:11,174
So your dad and both sisters
are in the military.

629
00:30:11,242 --> 00:30:12,375
Your brother's a cop.

630
00:30:12,443 --> 00:30:13,943
You must have felt
a lot of pressure

631
00:30:14,011 --> 00:30:17,546
to make certain choices
about your life, huh?

632
00:30:17,614 --> 00:30:20,882
- Sounds like you can relate.
- [Chuckles]

633
00:30:20,950 --> 00:30:22,852
I smell something.

634
00:30:22,919 --> 00:30:23,953
Seriously?
I mean, I--

635
00:30:24,020 --> 00:30:24,920
No.

636
00:30:28,625 --> 00:30:29,825
That S.U.V.

637
00:30:29,893 --> 00:30:31,927
He's not in there now,
but Bazevich--

638
00:30:31,995 --> 00:30:33,429
he was definitely in there.

639
00:30:33,497 --> 00:30:35,631
All right, all right,
all right.

640
00:30:35,699 --> 00:30:37,600
Who's next?
[Laughs]

641
00:30:39,169 --> 00:30:41,237
I am.

642
00:30:41,305 --> 00:30:43,339
[Crowd oohing]

643
00:30:43,407 --> 00:30:45,041
Nah, nah, nah, nah,
nah, nah, nah.

644
00:30:45,109 --> 00:30:47,043
Surprise.

645
00:30:48,427 --> 00:30:49,526
You trying to play me, Kat?

646
00:30:49,594 --> 00:30:51,061
I never said
I wasn't a fighter.

647
00:30:51,129 --> 00:30:53,402
There is gonna be
some action tonight!

648
00:30:53,502 --> 00:30:54,836
Place your bets!
Right now!

649
00:30:54,903 --> 00:30:56,504
Kat, this isn't
a good idea.

650
00:30:56,571 --> 00:31:00,107
Harken,
this isn't personal.

651
00:31:00,175 --> 00:31:01,475
All right, all right.
What you waiting for?

652
00:31:05,780 --> 00:31:09,115
In battle, a warrior
who remains calm

653
00:31:09,183 --> 00:31:11,117
and remembers their training

654
00:31:11,185 --> 00:31:15,054
will always vanquish a foe
who does not.

655
00:31:18,826 --> 00:31:21,628
Shift your opponent's weight
to one leg

656
00:31:21,696 --> 00:31:23,663
and attack
the weighted knee.

657
00:31:28,703 --> 00:31:30,070
If you lack size,

658
00:31:30,138 --> 00:31:32,640
compensate with speed
and precision.

659
00:31:40,482 --> 00:31:43,484
The brain
is the most sensitive organ

660
00:31:43,552 --> 00:31:45,720
in the human body.

661
00:31:47,290 --> 00:31:53,062
[Crowd shouting, cheering]

662
00:31:53,130 --> 00:31:54,997
Aah!

663
00:31:58,836 --> 00:32:00,770
[Cheering]

664
00:32:01,973 --> 00:32:05,376
Hey.
Hey, you all right?

665
00:32:05,443 --> 00:32:06,677
Is he okay?

666
00:32:06,745 --> 00:32:08,545
He's awesome.
Yeah, thanks.

667
00:32:08,613 --> 00:32:09,847
Hey, Harken.

668
00:32:09,915 --> 00:32:11,248
Harken.

669
00:32:11,316 --> 00:32:12,249
Come on.

670
00:32:12,317 --> 00:32:13,584
Not bad.

671
00:32:13,652 --> 00:32:17,787
Some people want to talk
to you about a job.

672
00:32:17,855 --> 00:32:20,256
- What kind of a job?
- Well, I don't know.

673
00:32:20,324 --> 00:32:23,126
They didn't say,
but I know they pay big.

674
00:32:23,193 --> 00:32:26,862
Hear 'em out.
Let 'em buy you a drink.

675
00:32:26,930 --> 00:32:30,099
Okay.

676
00:32:30,166 --> 00:32:32,634
You all right?

677
00:32:36,973 --> 00:32:39,074
Oh, that's that girl Kat
from the other night.

678
00:32:43,413 --> 00:32:45,481
Bill! Hicks!
Come on!

679
00:32:49,753 --> 00:32:50,720
What happened?

680
00:32:50,788 --> 00:32:52,054
You okay?

681
00:32:52,122 --> 00:32:53,322
- [Sighs]
- Ask him who did it.

682
00:32:53,390 --> 00:32:54,991
[Groans]
Hicks, I will kill you.

683
00:32:55,059 --> 00:32:57,027
Hey, listen,
we got a lead on Bazevich.

684
00:32:57,094 --> 00:32:58,495
He was in that car.
[Engine turns over]

685
00:32:58,562 --> 00:32:59,829
Oh, and your friend Kat
just got in there.

686
00:32:59,897 --> 00:33:01,297
All right, let's go.
Come on.

687
00:33:01,365 --> 00:33:03,299
[Tires squeal]

688
00:33:08,872 --> 00:33:12,141
That's their S.U.V.

689
00:33:12,209 --> 00:33:14,644
What the hell is this place?

690
00:33:14,712 --> 00:33:17,448
Okay, Bazevich is inside.

691
00:33:17,515 --> 00:33:19,716
You can smell him?

692
00:33:19,784 --> 00:33:21,385
Believe me,
he's unforgettable.

693
00:33:21,453 --> 00:33:22,854
Rachel,
what's going on in there?

694
00:33:22,921 --> 00:33:26,091
There's, uh...
[Heartbeats in distance]

695
00:33:26,158 --> 00:33:27,692
There's multiple heartbeats.

696
00:33:27,760 --> 00:33:33,031
An EKG, respirators,
hospital machines?

697
00:33:33,099 --> 00:33:35,868
The place is wired
with sensor alarms.

698
00:33:35,935 --> 00:33:38,370
I hear weaponry...
[Guns clack]

699
00:33:38,438 --> 00:33:41,406
And heavy boots.

700
00:33:41,474 --> 00:33:43,508
Unit One to tactical,
send backup to our position.

701
00:33:43,576 --> 00:33:45,510
Wait.
It's that girl Kat.

702
00:33:45,578 --> 00:33:50,215
No! Let me go!

703
00:33:50,283 --> 00:33:52,918
Her voice is weak.
She's fading.

704
00:33:52,985 --> 00:33:56,555
A male voice now.
"Make sure she stays under."

705
00:33:56,623 --> 00:33:59,124
They want to prep her
right away.

706
00:33:59,192 --> 00:34:00,592
Prep her for what?

707
00:34:00,660 --> 00:34:03,062
- I can't wait.
- Harken, wait!

708
00:34:03,129 --> 00:34:05,998
Damn it!

709
00:34:11,638 --> 00:34:14,339
Kat!

710
00:34:14,407 --> 00:34:15,974
Kat!
[Alarm blaring]

711
00:34:16,042 --> 00:34:17,642
Kat!

712
00:34:17,710 --> 00:34:20,512
[Gunshots]

713
00:34:20,580 --> 00:34:22,347
[Blaring continues]

714
00:34:26,252 --> 00:34:27,752
Harken!

715
00:34:29,922 --> 00:34:32,757
[Machine creaking]

716
00:34:51,043 --> 00:34:51,909
Kat!

717
00:34:58,784 --> 00:35:00,118
Kat!

718
00:35:00,186 --> 00:35:04,490
[Monitor beeping]

719
00:35:04,557 --> 00:35:05,891
Hey!

720
00:35:05,959 --> 00:35:07,860
- Bazevich?
- What are you doing?

721
00:35:07,928 --> 00:35:10,162
Kat!
Wait-unh!

722
00:35:10,230 --> 00:35:13,499
[Monitor beeping]

723
00:35:13,567 --> 00:35:16,334
Kat.

724
00:35:16,402 --> 00:35:17,702
Kat!
Harken...

725
00:35:17,770 --> 00:35:20,605
You're gonna be okay.

726
00:35:23,109 --> 00:35:24,776
Harken!

727
00:35:29,115 --> 00:35:31,157
Unh!

728
00:35:36,254 --> 00:35:38,823
Good job.

729
00:35:38,890 --> 00:35:41,192
Is she okay?

730
00:35:41,259 --> 00:35:43,694
- Kat...
- [Groans]

731
00:35:43,762 --> 00:35:45,263
You okay?

732
00:35:45,330 --> 00:35:48,966
I beat you.

733
00:35:49,034 --> 00:35:50,868
Yeah, you beat me.

734
00:35:50,935 --> 00:35:53,303
We'll need three ambulances

735
00:35:53,371 --> 00:35:54,704
and transport for prisoners
to Binghamton.

736
00:35:54,772 --> 00:35:58,008
104, gotcha.

737
00:35:58,076 --> 00:36:01,111
- So that's Bazevich.
- Hmm.

738
00:36:01,179 --> 00:36:02,446
The guy we've been chasing
the last two days

739
00:36:02,514 --> 00:36:04,414
is a dead man.

740
00:36:09,553 --> 00:36:12,355
Hey, turns out Bazevich
was a prisoner here too.

741
00:36:12,423 --> 00:36:15,359
Poetic justice
for killing Duffy, I guess.

742
00:36:15,427 --> 00:36:16,660
Can you believe it?

743
00:36:16,728 --> 00:36:18,296
Experimenting on Alphas.

744
00:36:18,363 --> 00:36:20,164
More like treating us
like animals.

745
00:36:20,232 --> 00:36:22,400
I could have gotten
out of there myself, you know.

746
00:36:22,468 --> 00:36:23,835
You know what?

747
00:36:23,903 --> 00:36:25,570
You can just say,
"Thank you so much,

748
00:36:25,638 --> 00:36:27,940
Bill Harken,
for rescuing me."

749
00:36:28,008 --> 00:36:30,142
I kicked your ass
once tonight.

750
00:36:30,210 --> 00:36:31,677
Do you want to go again?

751
00:36:31,745 --> 00:36:33,679
Easy does it, young lady.

752
00:36:33,747 --> 00:36:35,414
You're going to have to take it
easy for a while.

753
00:36:35,481 --> 00:36:36,849
You've been through quite
an ordeal.

754
00:36:36,916 --> 00:36:39,485
Just give me a couple weeks.
I won't remember.

755
00:36:39,552 --> 00:36:42,187
Hmm.

756
00:36:42,255 --> 00:36:44,356
I want to have a look
at you, too, later.

757
00:36:44,424 --> 00:36:46,425
No, no.
I'm--I'm fine. I'm fine.

758
00:36:46,492 --> 00:36:50,328
Look, I got to use my ability
and feel no downside, so...

759
00:36:50,396 --> 00:36:52,931
- No downside?
- No downside at all.

760
00:36:52,999 --> 00:36:55,734
Hey, Dr. Rosen,
who are you guys anyway?

761
00:36:55,801 --> 00:36:58,537
So Harken was undercover, right?
I wasn't undercover.

762
00:36:58,604 --> 00:36:59,872
You were
definitely undercover.

763
00:36:59,939 --> 00:37:02,508
And then he--he barged in
with those guys.

764
00:37:02,576 --> 00:37:03,776
We're consultants.

765
00:37:03,844 --> 00:37:05,144
We work with the government
now and then

766
00:37:05,212 --> 00:37:07,080
in situations
not unlike this one.

767
00:37:07,148 --> 00:37:08,882
You're Alpha Secret Agents,
right?

768
00:37:08,950 --> 00:37:10,350
- You're gonna be fine.
- You're Alpha secret agents.

769
00:37:10,418 --> 00:37:11,651
Just take it easy.

770
00:37:11,719 --> 00:37:14,487
- I to--I'm totally right.
- No, no.

771
00:37:14,555 --> 00:37:16,890
I'm right, right?

772
00:37:16,957 --> 00:37:18,892
You want me on your team.
I'm awesome.

773
00:37:31,738 --> 00:37:33,205
It's the perfect soap.

774
00:37:33,273 --> 00:37:35,540
It'll blend really well
with your natural scent,

775
00:37:35,608 --> 00:37:37,042
which, by the way, is--

776
00:37:37,109 --> 00:37:40,612
is really good
on its own anyway, so...

777
00:37:40,679 --> 00:37:41,813
there.

778
00:37:41,881 --> 00:37:45,217
Thanks.
Um, I'll try it.

779
00:37:45,284 --> 00:37:48,219
I was--I was,
uh, in the village,

780
00:37:48,287 --> 00:37:50,922
and I found it at this shop
next to my favorite restaurant,

781
00:37:50,990 --> 00:37:54,324
which is Italian.

782
00:37:54,392 --> 00:37:55,759
Oh.

783
00:38:04,602 --> 00:38:06,469
Do you like Italian?

784
00:38:09,539 --> 00:38:11,207
Um...

785
00:38:11,274 --> 00:38:14,310
Rachel, if--if we're going
to be working together--

786
00:38:14,377 --> 00:38:15,711
Right.

787
00:38:15,779 --> 00:38:19,415
Forget I mentioned it.

788
00:38:40,572 --> 00:38:42,573
What can I get you?

789
00:38:42,641 --> 00:38:45,176
Earl Grey tea, please.

790
00:38:45,244 --> 00:38:49,014
Okay.

791
00:38:49,082 --> 00:38:50,215
Hello, Lee.

792
00:38:50,283 --> 00:38:52,851
May I join you?

793
00:38:54,861 --> 00:38:57,529
You made it
very easy for me, Stanton.

794
00:38:57,995 --> 00:39:00,530
Or do you prefer Major Dunham?

795
00:39:00,598 --> 00:39:03,066
I prefer Stanton.

796
00:39:03,134 --> 00:39:06,203
Well, thank you for providing
Dr. Harrison's research.

797
00:39:06,270 --> 00:39:08,739
So you'd know how I began.

798
00:39:08,806 --> 00:39:11,241
Yes.
By murdering a friend.

799
00:39:13,311 --> 00:39:17,648
Dr. Harrison
wanted to use me.

800
00:39:17,716 --> 00:39:21,318
So you scarified
an innocent man.

801
00:39:21,385 --> 00:39:24,321
Have you ever sacrificed
an innocent man?

802
00:39:24,389 --> 00:39:26,022
Not intentionally.

803
00:39:26,090 --> 00:39:29,126
Every man must control
his own destiny.

804
00:39:31,763 --> 00:39:34,564
I reenlisted
after the doctor's death.

805
00:39:34,632 --> 00:39:36,766
I helped saved the Union.

806
00:39:36,834 --> 00:39:38,368
Hmm.

807
00:39:38,436 --> 00:39:39,636
So you're what--

808
00:39:39,704 --> 00:39:42,506
looking for the thanks
of a grateful nation?

809
00:39:42,574 --> 00:39:44,341
No.

810
00:39:44,409 --> 00:39:49,013
Just some understanding
of my unique perspective.

811
00:39:49,081 --> 00:39:52,050
I was shot again
at Cold Harbor

812
00:39:52,118 --> 00:39:54,186
and again at San Juan Hill,

813
00:39:54,253 --> 00:39:57,389
fought at Verdun,
in the streets of Berlin.

814
00:39:57,457 --> 00:39:59,024
Oh, a very impressive resume.

815
00:39:59,092 --> 00:40:00,993
Thank you.

816
00:40:02,930 --> 00:40:07,466
Every change brings bloodshed.

817
00:40:07,534 --> 00:40:10,403
We can stop that.

818
00:40:10,470 --> 00:40:12,705
And yet you say
a war is coming.

819
00:40:12,773 --> 00:40:15,175
Hmm.

820
00:40:15,243 --> 00:40:17,444
Because...

821
00:40:17,512 --> 00:40:20,847
[Liquid pouring]

822
00:40:20,915 --> 00:40:24,984
ordinary men react
with fear and violence

823
00:40:25,052 --> 00:40:27,186
to anything
that's new and different.

824
00:40:30,823 --> 00:40:32,357
You know,
one of my favorite subjects

825
00:40:32,425 --> 00:40:34,925
in medical school
was cellular research...

826
00:40:34,993 --> 00:40:36,260
Mmhmm.

827
00:40:36,328 --> 00:40:39,163
Examining the constituent
parts of things,

828
00:40:39,230 --> 00:40:42,533
trying to figure out
how it all...

829
00:40:42,601 --> 00:40:44,568
works together.

830
00:40:44,636 --> 00:40:46,804
It was very tedious,
but, um...

831
00:40:46,872 --> 00:40:50,975
It was exciting,
because eventually...

832
00:40:51,043 --> 00:40:54,145
I could see the whole picture.

833
00:40:57,683 --> 00:41:00,552
Try the tuna melt next time.

834
00:41:00,620 --> 00:41:03,054
It's excellent.

835
00:41:19,239 --> 00:41:21,540
No, Mom.
Don't do that.

836
00:41:21,608 --> 00:41:23,376
That's how I like it.

837
00:41:23,443 --> 00:41:25,311
Yeah, but that's the way
you keep it at home.

838
00:41:25,378 --> 00:41:28,047
No, this is home.
It's how I like it here.

839
00:41:28,115 --> 00:41:31,417
Right.

840
00:41:36,023 --> 00:41:37,223
Good night, Gary.

841
00:41:37,291 --> 00:41:41,862
Yeah, good night.

842
00:41:43,498 --> 00:41:45,265
Uh, Mom.

843
00:41:45,333 --> 00:41:46,467
Where'd you go?

844
00:41:46,534 --> 00:41:49,036
I'm right here.

845
00:41:51,239 --> 00:41:55,143
I'll call you at 8:00
after I scream,

846
00:41:55,210 --> 00:41:56,945
but before
I've had my breakfast.

847
00:41:59,115 --> 00:42:00,582
I'll answer.

848
00:42:00,650 --> 00:42:04,286
Yeah, okay.

849
00:42:10,993 --> 00:42:13,928
[Indistinct shouting,
loud impacts]

850
00:42:13,953 --> 00:42:17,953
== sync, corrected by <font color="#00ff00">elderman</font> ==

851
00:42:22,203 --> 00:42:24,104
Well, look who's back.

852
00:42:24,172 --> 00:42:25,973
Here to watch?

853
00:42:26,041 --> 00:42:29,143
Hell, no.
I'm here to fight.

